x4freetext: ABSTRACT GIVEN.
-NEUTRON CAPTURE CROSS-SECTION RATIOS OF PU-240,
PU-242,U-238 AND AU-197,IN THE ENERGY RANGE FROM
10 TO 90 KEV-
KARLSRUHE 3 MV PULSED ACCELERATOR,WHICH
PROVIDED PROTON 10 TO 20 KEV ABOVE THE N-SOURCE
REACTION THRESHOLD,THAT IS 1.881 MEV.
.THE PROTON BEAM WAS PULSED WITH A REPETITION RATE OF
2.5 MHZ AND A PULSE WIDTH OF 700 PSEC.
GAVE KINEMATICALLY COLLIMATED NEUTRONS UP TO
MAXIMUM ENERGY OF 90 KEV.
.THE 1891 KEV PROTONS GAVE AN OPENING ANGLE OF HALF
THE NEUTRON CONE OF 30 DEGREES,WHILE 1901 KEV PROTONS
GAVE A 45 DEGREE ANGLE,FOR THE SAME QUANTITY.
.AN AVERAGE BEAM CURRENT OF 15 MICROA GAVE AT A 10 CM
DISTANCE FROM THE LI-TARGET A FLUX OF 6*10**4
NEUTRONS/SEC*CM**2.
.THE PU OXYDE POWER WAS ENCLOSED IN A 0.1 MM THICK
STAINLESS STEEL CAN AND WAS WELDED IN A 0.3 MM THICK
POLYETHYLENE FOIL.
.AN EMPTY DUMMY CAN WAS USED FOR CORRECTION OF CAPTURE
DATA FOR CAPTURE AND SCATTERING EVENTS IN THE CAN.
.A GRAPHITE SAMPLE WAS USED TO CORRECT DATA FROM
CAPTURE EVENTS IN THE SURROUNDING MATERIAL,CAUSED
BY NEUTRONS SCATTERED BY THE SAMPLE.
.FOUR SAMPLES WERE MOUNTED ON A SAMPLE CHANGER MOVING
THE SAMPLES IN A DIRECTION PERPENDICULAR TO THE BEAM
AXIS. THE SAMPLES WERE CYCLED AUTOMATICALLY TO THE
MEASURING POSITION IN THE NEUTRON CONE IN EQUAL
INTERVALS,DEFINED BY A PROTON BEAM INTEGRATOR,WHICH
INITIATED A SAMPLE CHANGE AFTER A TOTAL CHARGE OF
8*10**-3 COULOMB WAS ACCUMULATED ON THE TARGET
(I.E.TIME INTERV=10 MN).
.THE FOLLOWING TABLE COMPILES THE RELEVANT SAMPLE DATA.
SAMPLE CHEM.C.ISOTOPIC COMPOSIT.(PC) WEIGH.THICK.BIND.
GRAMS (MM) EN.KEV
C     GRAPHITE NATURAL COMPOSITION  6.044  5.0 ------
TOF TECHNIQUE USED WITH VERY SHORT FLIGHT PATH
(ABOUT 10 CM),GIVING A HIGH NEUTRON FLUX AND THEREFORE
AN OPTIMAL SIGNAL-TO-BACKGROUND RATIO.
.EIGHT RUNS WERE MADE WITH THE FOLLOWING CARACTERISTICS
RUN NO SAMPLE1 SAMPLE2 SAMPLE3 SAMPLE4 FLIGHT P.(MM)
II     PU-240  DUMMY    U-235   AU-197    135
III    DUMMY    ---     U-235    ---      135
VIII   DUMMY    ---     U-235    ---       68.5.
.A SPECIAL RUN WITH A FLIGHT PATH OF 1MM WAS PERFORMED
WITH THE U-235 SAMPLE TO MEASURE THE TIME DISTRIBUTION
OF THE FISSION NEUTRONS FOR THEIR FLIGHT PATH BETWEEN
SAMPLE AND DETECTOR.
0.75 MM THICK LEAD ABSORBER IN FRONT OF A 20 MM
THICK GRAPHITE CONVERTER WHICH PROVIDED,BY MEANS
OF GAMMA-RAY INTERACTION,ELECTRONS DETECTED BY A 0.5
MM THICK NE-104 PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR,90 MM IN DIAM.
ITS NOMINAL TIME RESOLUTION WAS 106 NSEC.
A NE-213 LIQUID SCINTILLATOR,100 MM IN DIAM,
AND 30 MM THICK,DETECTED PROMPT NEUTRONS USING PULSE
SHAPE DISCRIMINATOR EQUIPMENT TO SEPARATE FAST NEUTRON
AND GAMMA-RAYS.
ITS NOMINAL TIME RESOLUTION WAS 1.4 NSEC.
.THESE TWO DETECTORS WERE LOCATED OUTSIDE THE NEUTRON
CONE AT AN ANGLE OF 120 DEGREES TO THE BEAM AXIS,AND
WERE SHIELDED WITH LEAD FROM GAMMAS PRODUCED IN THE
NEUTRON TARGET AND IN THE SAMPLES.
A LI-6 GLASS DETECTOR WAS PLACED AT A 630 MM
DISTANCE FROM THE NEUTRON TARGET.
IT SERVED AS A MONITOR FOR THE NEUTRON FLUX AND WAS
USED FOR DETERMINATION AND CONTINUOUS CONTROL OF THE
MAXIMUM NEUTRON ENERGY.
.THE CAPTURE CROSS-SECTION RATIO WERE CALCULATED BY
THE EQUATION
SIG(I) = C(I).(MS*SS)(R).N(R).B(R) ,
SIG(R)   C(R) (MS*SS)(I) N(I) B(I)
WHERE C() ARE THE BACKGROUND CORRECTED COUNT RATES ,
MS*SS CORRECTION FOR MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND
SELF SHIELDING,DETERMINED BY THE MONTE
CARLO CODE SESH,SEE GA 8380,1968,GULFGA,
N() NUMBER OF ATOMS PER SAMPLE               ,
B() NEUTRON BINDING ENERGY                   ,
(I) REFERS TO THE ISOTOPE UNDER INVESTIGATION,
(R) REFERS TO THE REFERENCE SAMPLE.
Gamma
FISSION EVENTS DETECTED BY THE PROMPT FISSION
NEUTRONS.
.A MORE COMPLETE ANALYSIS ON THE METHOD WAS GIVEN.
.COMPARISON WITH OTHER DATA,AND CURVES GIVEN.
.DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR,
-TIME DEPENDANT AND INDEPENDANT BACKGROUND,
-FISSION EVENTS AND CAPTURES IN THE IMPURITY ISOTOPES
PRESENT IN PU SAMPLES,
-MULTIPLE CORRECTION AND SELF-SHIELDING EFFECTS.
.NEW CALCULATIONS SHOW THAT THERE IS A DEVIATION
OF THE DETECTOR EFFICIENCY FROM A LINEAR INCREASE
WITH GAMMA-RAY ENERGY. IT WAS SUPPOSED BEFORE
THAT THE SHAPE OF THE CAPTURE GAMMA-RAY SPECTRA
OF THE HEAVY NUCLEI FROM AU-197 TO AM-241 DID
NOT DIFFER TOO MUCH, WHICH WAS FOUND TO BE
WRONG AND CORRECTION FACTORS HAVE BEEN COMMUNI-
CATED BY THE AUTHORS.
STATISTICAL ERROR.
.STATISTICAL UNCERTAINTIES WERE DIRECTLY DETERMINED
BY THE RESPECTIVE COUNT RATES.
SYSTEMATIC ERROR.
.THE SYSTEMATIC UNCERTAINTIES WERE COMPOSED OF
-FLIGHT PATH UNCERTAINTIES,
-TIME DEPENDENT BACKGROUND UNCERTAINTIES,
-CONSTANT BACKGROUND,
-NEUTRON SCATTERING IN THE POLYETHYLENE FOIL,
-UNCERTAINTIES DUE TO DIFFERENCES IN THE EFFICIENCIES
FOR FISSION GAMMA RAYS IN THE MOXON-RAE DETECTOR,AND
FOR FISSION NEUTRONS IN THE FISSION DETECTOR,
-UNCERTAINTIES FROM THE UNFOLDING PROCEDURE APPLIED
TO THE FISSION NEUTRON SPECTRA TO CORRECT FOR THE
SHIFT AND SPREAD OF THE FISSION NEUTRON TIME
DISTRIBUTION ON THE PATH BETWEEN SAMPLE AND DETECTOR,
-UNCERTAINTIES DUE TO MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND
SELF-SHIELDING CORRECTIONS,
-UNCERTAINTIES ISSUED FROM NEUTRON FLUX VARIATIONS,
-MOXON-RAE EFFICIENCY,
-ISOTOPIC IMPURITIES,
-NEUTRON ENERGY INTERVAL DETERMINATION.
THE COMPLETE DETAILS OF THIS SYSTEMATIC ERROR ANALYSIS
ARE GIVEN IN TABLES 7 AND 8 OF THE MAIN REFERENCE.
TOTAL ERROR.
.DATA HAVE BEEN RECALCULATED WITH NEW CORR. FACTORS.
G.C.,  REACTION STRINGS CORRECTED.
